tant version of the Tristan story available more widely. It also includes an introduction, listing of illuminations, bibliography and explanatory notes. Gloria Allaire is Assistant Professor of Italian at theUniversity of Kentucky.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArthurian romances. 0aRomances, ItalianvTranslations into English. 0aTristan (Legendary character)vRomances. 4aMedieval Literature. 7aPOETRY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAccademia Nazionale dei Lincei.  aBiblioteca Corsiniana.  aDinadan.  aGloria Allaire.  aItalian.  aKing Arthur.  aLancelot.  aManuscript.  aNortheast Italy.  aTournament.  aTristan Story.  aTristano Corsiniano.  aUniversity of Kentucky.1 aAllaire, Gloria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAllaire, Gloria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311143132140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204455040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782044550423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782044550/original  a978-3-11-143132-1  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles